# onboarding/company.md — Alpha Anywhere context cache

> The assistant reads Alpha's canonical KB pages and caches a compact
> summary here so it has company context in every session without
> re-reading the full files. **Edit the KB markdown, not this file** —
> the local copy refreshes automatically on each `scripts/sync-kb` run.

## Canonical sources in the KB

| File | What it tells you | KB path |
|---|---|---|
| **Operating Framework** | How Alpha works — decision norms, rituals, operating cadence | `operating-framework/README.md` (entry point; sub-files linked from it) |
| **Team directory** | Who works at Alpha, their roles, what they own | `core/people/` (one file per person) + `archive/teams/<team>.md` |
| **New Hire Onboarding plans** | Per-employee onboarding plans. Used for new hires only. | `archive/onboarding/<email-slug>.md` |
| **Department templates** | Department-specific onboarding scaffolds | `archive/onboarding/_templates/` |

## What gets cached here after first session

After the first real session, this file holds a compact summary the
assistant maintains itself:

### Mission (one paragraph, from Operating Framework)
*(filled automatically)*

### How Alpha decides (from Operating Framework)
*(filled automatically)*

### Rituals + cadences (from Operating Framework)
*(filled automatically)*

### Glossary — abbreviations & internal terms
*(filled automatically — growable as the user encounters new terms)*

### Who's who — leaders + scope (from `core/people/`)
*(filled automatically — top-of-funnel only, full list lives in
`core/people/`. Filter by `role` containing `lead`/`director`/`head`
or by being listed as `lead` on a `core/teams` row.)*

## Refresh cadence

- **On every session start:** after `scripts/sync-kb`, compare the most
  recent commit touching `operating-framework/`, `core/people/`, or
  `core/teams/` against the timestamp written below. If newer, re-cache.
- **On demand:** user says *"refresh Alpha context"* → re-cache all
  sources above.
- **Monthly:** full re-cache regardless, to absorb additions.

## Last synced

*(auto — timestamp + last-seen commit SHA written after each successful
sync)*
